00:21:43,235 --> 00:21:44,429
And then you came back.

489
00:21:44,503 --> 00:21:47,768
Which makes you
the biggest liar
of history.

490
00:21:47,839 --> 00:21:49,306
I don't see it
that way.

491
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:52,702
Do you want to
hear a lie?

492
00:21:52,778 --> 00:21:53,767
What?

493
00:21:53,845 --> 00:21:55,210
I think you're great.

494
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:57,145
You're my best friend.

495
00:22:01,386 --> 00:22:03,513
Hey, do you mind
if we make a stop
on the way home?

496
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:05,054
Sure.
Cool.

497
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:10,727
What are we doing at
your parents' house?

498
00:22:10,796 --> 00:22:12,559
I have a surprise for you.

499
00:22:12,631 --> 00:22:14,895
All right. Ready?
Close your eyes.

500
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:18,593
And now, open your eyes.

501
00:22:19,571 --> 00:22:20,765
Ta-da!

502
00:22:22,574 --> 00:22:24,940
I don't get it.

503
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:26,136
I bought it.

504
00:22:27,913 --> 00:22:29,312
It's ours.

505
00:22:32,651 --> 00:22:35,552
Let's go inside.
I'll show you inside.

506
00:22:37,255 --> 00:22:39,587
So if you can believe it,
I did it without a realtor.

507
00:22:39,658 --> 00:22:42,889
Saving on
closing costs
is good.

508
00:22:42,961 --> 00:22:46,761
And we can put
all the money
to de-shag the carpet.

509
00:22:48,433 --> 00:22:52,233
Which I think will
help the color situation.

510
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:57,472
Yeah,
I am really sorry
about this.

511
00:22:57,542 --> 00:23:01,034
I tried to move it,
but he is really
nailed in there.

512
00:23:01,613 --> 00:23:03,547
Worried about
art theft, I guess.

513
00:23:03,615 --> 00:23:06,106
A lot of art thieves
in this neighborhood.

514
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:14,217
This is the master bedroom,
but I'm actually
not allowed in here.

515
00:23:14,292 --> 00:23:17,125
So, I'm still in the process
of converting the garage.

516
00:23:17,195 --> 00:23:19,129
It's got great light
in here.

517
00:23:19,197 --> 00:23:24,157
And I was thinking
it could be perfect
for an art studio.

518
00:23:35,180 --> 00:23:37,410
Look, I know.

519
00:23:37,482 --> 00:23:39,040
I bought this
without asking you.

520
00:23:39,117 --> 00:23:42,848
And it doesn't look great.
I know that.

521
00:23:43,655 --> 00:23:47,352
And if you really hate it,
I totally understand.
It's just...

522
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:48,757
I love it.

523
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:51,957
You do?

524
00:23:52,030 --> 00:23:54,157
Yeah, I love it.

525
00:23:54,232 --> 00:23:55,221
Really?

526
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:56,767
I mean,
you bought me a house.

527
00:23:56,835 --> 00:23:57,961
Oh, my God.

528
00:23:58,036 --> 00:23:59,594
You bought me a house!

529
00:24:00,739 --> 00:24:02,138
Yeah, I did.

530
00:24:10,515 --> 00:24:13,575
Do we have to sleep
in your parents' bedroom?

531
00:24:13,652 --> 00:24:16,780
No. No, we'll just
board that up.

532
00:24:16,855 --> 00:24:20,347
It'll be that
weird spare room
that people ask us about.

533
00:24:20,425 --> 00:24:21,551
And the clown?

534
00:24:21,626 --> 00:24:23,890
Yeah, I really
can't move him.

535
00:24:26,198 --> 00:24:27,825
What is my perfect crime?

536
00:24:27,899 --> 00:24:30,129
I break into Tiffany's
at midnight.

537
00:24:30,202 --> 00:24:34,070
Do I go for the vault?
No, I go for the chandelier.
It's priceless.

538
00:24:34,172 --> 00:24:36,299
As I'm taking it down,
a woman catches me.

539
00:24:36,374 --> 00:24:37,602
She tells me to stop.

540
00:24:37,676 --> 00:24:39,701
It's her father's business.
She's Tiffany.

541
00:24:39,778 --> 00:24:42,110
I say no.
We make love all night.

542
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:45,308
In the morning, the cops come
and I escape
in one of their uniforms.

543
00:24:45,383 --> 00:24:46,850
I tell her to
meet me in Mexico,

544
00:24:46,918 --> 00:24:49,148
but I go to Canada.
I don't trust her.

545
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:51,485
Besides, I like the cold.

546
00:24:51,556 --> 00:24:53,046
30 years later,
I get a postcard.

547
00:24:53,124 --> 00:24:55,684
I have a son and
he's the chief of police.

548
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:57,660
This is where
the story gets interesting.

549
00:24:57,729 --> 00:25:01,529
I tell Tiffany
to meet me in Paris
by the Trocadero.

550
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:03,090
She's been waiting
for me all these years.

551
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:04,760
She's never
taken another lover.

552
00:25:04,836 --> 00:25:07,134
I don't care.
I don't show up.
I go to Berlin.

553
00:25:07,205 --> 00:25:09,935
That's where
I stashed the chandelier.

